HEADWORD: Marauder
<hw>Ma*raud`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Maraud</er>, <pos>v.</pos>: cf. F. <ets>maraudeur</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A rover in quest of booty or plunder; a plunderer; one who
pillages.</def> <rj><au>De Quincey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

